data.text:
Friday April 26 2013, 1.01am ,

Jeff Barak, Editor-in-Chief, Jerusalem Post, 1996–2002, 52; John Battle, politician, 62; the Marquess of Bute, racing car driver, 55; Sir Edward Cazalet, a High Court Judge, Family Division, 1988-2000, 77; Joan Chen, actress, 52; David Coleman, sports commentator, 87; Howard Davies, theatre director, 68; Sir Gordon Downey, Comptroller and Auditor General, 1981-87, 85; Duane Eddy, guitarist, 75; Justin Gosling, principal, St Edmund Hall, Oxford, 1982-96, 83; Professor Sir James Holt, master, Fitzwilliam College, Cambridge, 1981-88, 91; Maurice Isaac, former headmaster, 85; Lord Justice Jacob, a Lord Justice of Appeal, 2003-11, 72; Marianne Jean-Baptiste, actress, 46; Sir Richard Nichols, Lord Mayor of London, 1997-98, 75; Dame Margaret Scott, founding director, Australian Ballet School, 91; Sister Margaret Shepherd, former director, Council of Christians and Jews, 69;
